President Obama delivered a eulogy at the Upper Big Branch Mine Memorial Service, honoring the 29 miners who lost their lives in a mining disaster. He emphasized that these miners worked hard and faced hardships, all for the sake of their families and the pursuit of the American dream. The president received numerous letters and emails from people connected to the mining community, expressing their pride in being part of a mining family and urging him to ensure such tragedies do not happen again. President Obama acknowledged that while they cannot bring back the lost miners, their task on Earth is to prevent future tragedies and ensure the safety of miners. He emphasized the importance of treating miners like family and working collectively to achieve this goal, as we are all Americans.